  <name>grunner</name>
  <summary>A fast, keyboard-driven application launcher for GNOME</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      grunner is a rofi-like application launcher for GNOME and other Linux desktops,
      written in Rust. Built on GTK4 and libadwaita, it follows your system's light/dark
      theme and accent color automatically.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Fuzzy application search with fuzzy matching</li>
      <li>Colon commands for file search (:f), full-text grep (:fg), GNOME Shell search providers (:s), and Obsidian integration (:ob, :obg)</li>
      <li>Obsidian integration: open vault, create notes, daily notes, quick notes</li>
      <li>GNOME Shell search providers: query any installed GNOME Shell search provider</li>
      <li>Power bar: suspend, restart, power off, and log out with confirmation</li>
      <li>Themeable using libadwaita CSS custom properties</li>
      <li>Configurable via TOML file</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
